The paper discusses network intrusion detection systems, which are primarily related to computer security (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses software architecture and implementation, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper describes the use of a hardware-based network processor, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY).
